<p class="head">18<sup>th</sup> August Continued</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">all Day<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[W]</span>e Came Up with the 2 Canoes that left <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> them that they went very Slowly, but they thou<span class="AddHand-editors">[ght]</span> <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> they were doing Wonders, and going Exceeding well Co<span class="AddHand-editors">[nsi]</span>dering the hardships they met with, and begun Cursing <span class="AddHand-editors">[them]</span>selves for Blockheads, for Coming to this Infernal par<span class="AddHand-editors">[t]</span> of the Country, as they Call'd it, Damning the firs<span class="AddHand-editors">[t]</span> person that attempted this road, where they Could no<span class="AddHand-editors">[t]</span> ge<span class="AddHand-editors">[t]</span> a Drink of Clean water to Quench their Thirst<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[I]</span> did not m<span class="AddHand-editors">[ind]</span> that much, as I Knew it to be their Custom, whenever the<span class="AddHand-editors">[y]</span> met with Any uncommon hardship, and as those that Spoke, were proude North bucks that never had been this way before, and very good Able Men, I did not a<span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> to hurt their Pride, by representing to them all at O<span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> how Easy they <span class="AddHand-author">were</span> dispirited, so I began to Chear them <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> and told them to Consider that this was not the On<span class="AddHand-editors">[ly]</span> Road in which people met with unuseal hardship this year, Owing to the lowness of the Water, which was the Same all Over the Country<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>hey agreed wi<span class="AddHand-editors">[th]</span> me in allowing the lowness of the water would a<span class="AddHand-editors">[dd]</span> greatly to the Carrying in Every part of the Cou<span class="AddHand-editors">[ntry]</span></p>

